==English==
===Interjection===
[[Category:English interjections]]
'''crikey!'''

#Used [[euphemistically]] for '''[[Christ]]''' as a mild expression of surprise. Esp. in Australia, and often in Britain

#Used as an exclamation, or as an emphasis of fact at the conclusion of a statement, as in "It's a hot day today, by Crikey!"

#Often used with Moses, similar to crikey on it's own, especially in Australia, "Crikey moses!"
 
====Synonyms====
*[[criminy]], [[cripes]]